```plantuml
@startuml ertis-research_lwm2m-blockchain

title LwM2M-Blockchain Integration System\nArchitectural View: Connectivity & Control Flow

skinparam componentStyle uml2
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam nodesep 20
skinparam ranksep 30

package "Frontend" {
    [Anomaly Detection UI] as anomaly_ui
    [Management UI] as mgmt_ui
}

package "Backend" {
    [REST API] as rest_api
    [Business Logic] as business_logic
    [Web3j Adapter] as web3j
}

package "Blockchain" {
    [Ethereum Node] as ethereum
    [UserStore SC] as user_sc
    [ClientStore SC] as client_sc
    [AnomalyStore SC] as anomaly_sc
}

package "LwM2M" {
    [LwM2M Server] as lwm2m_server
    [Bootstrap Server] as bootstrap
    [LwM2M Client] as lwm2m_client
}

package "Evaluation" {
    [Jupyter Notebooks] as evaluation
}

' Connectivity
anomaly_ui --> rest_api : HTTP/REST\n(device data)
mgmt_ui --> rest_api : HTTP/REST\n(user mgmt)

rest_api --> business_logic : method calls
business_logic --> web3j : contract calls
web3j --> ethereum : JSON-RPC

business_logic --> lwm2m_server : HTTP/REST\n(client reg)
lwm2m_server --> lwm2m_client : CoAP\n(monitoring)
lwm2m_client --> bootstrap : CoAP\n(bootstrapping)
bootstrap --> client_sc : Web3j\n(security info)

' Control Flow Annotations
note top of anomaly_ui
Triggers anomaly detection flow:
1. Fetches device data
2. Displays anomalies
3. Stores via backend
end note

note right of lwm2m_server
Control flow:
1. Monitors devices
2. Processes data
3. Updates blockchain
end note

note left of bootstrap
Security flow:
1. Gets config from blockchain
2. Bootstraps clients
end note

@enduml
```